duck: Peak Reverse Voltage, a characteristic of diodes
Pressure relief valve - A pressure relief valve is a safety device that relieves overpressure in a vessel or piping.
Pressure reducing valve - A pressure regulator is a valve that automatically cuts off the flow of a liquid or gas at a certain pressure.
PRV, the abbreviation for "Preverb", a name to describe certain elements prefixed to verbs in some languages
PRV engine, an automobile V6 engine developed by Peugeot Renault and Volvo
Pearl River Valley Railroad - The Pearl River Valley Railroad was a shortline railroad that ran from Nicholson to Picayune, Mississippi.
